You might be able to squeeze a bit more out of the PGN handling by using visitors (which avoid an expensive copy that `node.board()` has to make).

```python
class MyVisitor(chess.pgn.BaseVisitor):
    def visit_move(self, board, move):
        # called in order for each move of the game 
        pass

game.accept(Visitor())
```

Or even skipping the creation of the game representation in memory and analysing moves directly as they get parsed:

```python
class MyVisitor(chess.pgn.BaseVisitor):
    def __init__(self):
        self.found_game = False

    def begin_game(self):
        self.found_game = True

    def visit_move(self, board, move):
        # called in order for each move of the game 
        pass

    def result(self):
        return self.found_game

more_games = True
while more_games:
    more_games = chess.pgn.read_game(Visitor=MyVisitor)
```

