So here is a gist of what I'm gonna do.

First check for nix just as now by compiling the cpp code with `#include <nix.hpp>` and we can get the nix version from here if we define a macro as I mentioned above or otherwise we can get version by parsing `nix.pc` in Unix systems.

```cpp
    #include <nix.hpp>

    int main() {
        cout << NIX_LIB_VERSION; 
        return 0;
    }
```

Then we can check that boost-python is installed for currently running Python version. If boost-python is found, then we can check if `nixpy version == nix version` as mentioned in #209 and build the bindings. If any of cases failed we can stop the installation there.

