@bacongobbler Could we possibly transparently migrate `registrationEnabled` to `registrationMode` and delete the key, so that everybody is eventually up to date?

I agree there is sense to respecting it, though, but it is hard to tell if the user is using the registration enabled setting. For example, a user used to have registration enabled in a old version of deis, so`registrationEnabled` is set to `False`. Later, on the current version of deis, he decided to renable registration, and sets it to `registraionEnabled` to `enabled`. How can we tell which to respect?

To make matters worse, whether or not anybody is using them, `registrationEnabled` and `registrationMode` both have default values. If the user upgrades, both of them set and it will be really tricky to tell which one the user intentds us to use.

